page.title: 06Cubs & Brownies - W.Windsor
page.content: There are two{cub}packs in the{5th {Windsor Scout Group.}They meet on Mondays and Fridays at the Scout Hut in Wolf Lane. They wear a red scarf with a green edging. The uniform can be quite expensive but it is possible to buy it second-hand. The Cubs play games and work for badges. They go swimming at Maidenhead and camping at Bears Rails. There is a waiting list to join. There are two{Brownie}packs which meet on Tuesdays at All Saints' Church Centre and on Wednesdays at the Scout Hut. They also play games and work for badges. The Brownies have an inspection every week. They go camping and have parties. They go to Church Parade once a month. There are two, three or four adults helping with each pack.
